menuconfig RUNTIME_BLE
	bool "runtime-ble: trouble-based loadable BLE runtime (prebuilt staticlib)"
	default n
	depends on !BT
	select DYNAMIC_THREAD
	select DYNAMIC_THREAD_ALLOC
	select DYNAMIC_INTERRUPTS
	select HWINFO
	help
	  trouble (Rust) BLE host + nRF SoftDevice Controller, packaged as a per-chip
	  prebuilt staticlib (lib/<chip>/libruntime_ble.a) plus the Zephyr glue
	  (glue/glue.c). It exposes a generic Nordic-UART-style GATT peripheral
	  (RX write + TX notify) via a small C API (include/runtime_ble.h).

	  The library OWNS the radio, so the application MUST build with CONFIG_BT=n
	  and CONFIG_MPSL=n (enforced by `depends on !BT`). Runtime state is
	  heap-allocated on runtime_ble_load() and freed on runtime_ble_unload(), so
	  it costs ~no RAM until loaded. Set CONFIG_HEAP_MEM_POOL_SIZE large enough to
	  hold one session (~40 KB incl. the dynamic thread stack), and select the
	  dynamic-stack-from-heap strategy with CONFIG_DYNAMIC_THREAD_PREFER_ALLOC=y
	  (a choice symbol, so it must be set in the application prj.conf).

if RUNTIME_BLE

config RUNTIME_BLE_THREAD_STACK_SIZE
	int "BLE runtime thread stack size (bytes)"
	default 32768
	range 16384 65536
	help
	  Dynamic stack (k_thread_stack_alloc) for the thread that runs the trouble
	  async host. Steady-state high-water is ~14 KB, but the MPSL/SDC C-library
	  init transient is deeper: 32768 is reliable, 24576 is the tested minimum.
	  Allocated from the heap on load, freed on unload.

config RUNTIME_BLE_THREAD_PRIORITY
	int "BLE runtime thread priority"
	default 5
	range 0 15
	help
	  Preemptible priority (K_PRIO_PREEMPT) for the BLE runtime thread.

config RUNTIME_BLE_CENTRAL
	bool "Enable the central role (scan/connect + GATT client)"
	default n
	help
	  Links the central-capable prebuilt staticlib
	  (lib/<chip>/libruntime_ble_central.a) and enables the central API
	  (runtime_ble_scan_start / runtime_ble_connect / runtime_ble_client_*).

	  Off by default so peripheral-only apps stay lean: the central role adds
	  the scan/central SoftDevice Controller features (extra flash/RAM). The
	  matching staticlib must exist for the target chip — build it with the
	  `central` Cargo feature (see rust/README.md).

endif # RUNTIME_BLE
